# Development: `vite` loads `.env`, `.env.local`, `.env.development`, etc.
# If your key only lives in `.env.production`, it is merged automatically during `npm run dev`
# (see `web/vite.config.ts`). You can also set either variable below in `.env.local`.
#
# Backend (see `web/src/lib/apiOrigin.ts`):
# - Production / static builds: set VITE_API_ORIGIN (no trailing slash), e.g. https://api.example.com
# - Local `vite` dev proxy: optional VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET if not using default; can point at a remote API.
# VITE_API_ORIGIN=
# VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8000
NEXT_PUBLIC_LOGO_DEV_KEY=
#
# Optional alias (same value). Supported for teams that prefer the Vite convention:
# VITE_LOGO_DEV_KEY=
#
# Server-only secret for Logo.dev API calls — do not reference in React; add when you add server routes.
# LOGO_DEV_SECRET=
